    "liar_game_data": {
        "topic": "German False Friends",
        "question": "Your German friend says 'Ich bekomme ein neues Auto.' What does this mean?",
        "options": [
            "I am becoming a new car",
            "I am receiving/getting a new car",
            "I am buying a new car",
            "I am selling a new car"
        ],
        "correct_answer_index": 1,
        "explanation": "The German verb 'bekommen' is a classic false friend for English speakers. It means 'to get' or 'to receive,' NOT 'to become.' The German word for 'to become' is 'werden.' This is one of the most common mistakes English speakers make when learning German, as the words look and sound similar but have completely different meanings."
    }
